title: No Cash - Run Your Pockets
description:
No Cash were a political riot ska-core band that burst into the late nineties scene with cutting riffs and lyrics that spoke of injustice and hate across the globe. Their songs are anthems to many revolutionary and impoverished teenagers everywhere and often compared to Leftover Crack, Choking Victim and INDK.

No Cash Has sold over 1,000 copies of their only album and are continuing to gain popularity.

As of early 2005, they have broken up.


Run Your Pockets
Released on August 12, 2003
